TRUE(1)                        User Commands                        TRUE(1)

NAME
    true - do nothing, successfully

SYNOPSIS
    true [IGNORED]...

DESCRIPTION
    Exit with a status of 0. All arguments are ignored. Useful as a
    placeholder or to force a success status in a script.

    This is the unmodified GNU coreutils true(1), ported to Horus and run as
    a ring-3 program from /bin/true.

EXIT STATUS
    Always 0.

SEE ALSO
    false(1), hier(7)
